verbs.description: enure (third-person singular simple present enures, present participle enuring, simple past and past participle enured)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To inure; to make accustomed or desensitized to something unpleasant due to constant exposure.
(intransitive, chiefly law) To take effect, to be operative; used with to.
examples: All our striving enures to our own spiritual benefit.
